{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6d7b79e4-fed3-44fe-be1a-be6daba5684f","content":"Use **`dotnet run`**, not `dotnet test`.\n\nHot reload via `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` works with the **Microsoft Testing Platform** runner, which is invoked when you run the test project as an executable. `dotnet test` uses the traditional VSTest infrastructure and won't activate the hot reload pipeline.\n\nRun it like:\n\n```bash\ndotnet run --project TestProject.csproj\n```\n\nSince you have `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` enabled, `dotnet test` will delegate to the new platform too — but hot reload specifically requires the `dotnet run` (or direct executable) entry point so the file watcher can rebuild and re-execute on changes.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f2216a9f-a36c-45bd-bbc6-88673576ccac","outputTokens":163},"id":"f9a202e8-8061-47f1-b70a-499ba4350020","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:46:23.843Z","parentId":"7a99395f-db11-4cb1-ace5-f2814a5151e0"}
